    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ADJUST/INSTALL - ADJUST RING GEAR BACKLASH</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ADJUST RING GEAR BACKLASH</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Measure backlash with a dial indicator. The indicator should be positioned on a ring gear tooth, at
                the extreme heel end, perpendicular to the tooth surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401644">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401644" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401644" filename="../figg14/G1401644.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Measuring Backlash</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="hl1401612">
            <title>Backlash Specifications (Normal)</title>
            <table id="hl1401613">
                <title>Backlash Specifications (Normal)</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.49in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.49in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.49in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="1to3"/>
                    <thead valign="bottom">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="1to3" valign="bottom" align="center">
                                <para>BACKLASH SPECIFICATIONS (Normal)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>New Gearing:</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Early Axle Series 15 through 18</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>0.006" to 0.016"</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Late Axle Models 15040T/P through 19055T/P</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(0.15 to 0.41mm)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Early Axle Series 21 through 35</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>0.008" to 0.018"</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Late Axle Models 21085T/P through 35055T/P</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(0.20 to 0.46mm)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For new gearing, check ring gear backlash after each shim change and adjust if necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Used Gearing:</emph>
                Reset to normal backlash recorded before disassembly.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">To REMOVE backlash:</emph>
                Loosen the adjuster on the teeth side of the ring gear several notches. Tighten the opposite adjuster
                one notch.
            </para>
            <para>Tighten adjuster on teeth side of ring gear until it contacts the bearing cup. Continue tightening the
                same adjuster 2 or 3 notches. Recheck backlash.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">To ADD backlash:</emph>
                Loosen the adjuster on the teeth side of the ring gear several notches. Loosen the opposite adjuster one
                notch.
            </para>
            <para>Tighten adjuster on teeth side of ring gear until it contacts the bearing cup. Continue tightening the
                same adjuster 2 or 3 notches. Recheck backlash.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
